            "questionText": "<p>A company needs to monitor its websiteâ€™s availability to end users. The company needs a solution to provide an Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) notification if the website's uptime decreases to less than 99%. The monitoring must provide an accurate view of the user experience on the website.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>ğŸ“ <strong><u>TÃ³m táº¯t Ä‘á»:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>CÃ´ng ty cáº§n giÃ¡m sÃ¡t <strong>tÃ­nh kháº£ dá»¥ng (availability)</strong> website tá»« gÃ³c Ä‘á»™ <strong>ngÆ°á»i dÃ¹ng cuá»‘i</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>YÃªu cáº§u nháº­n <strong>thÃ´ng bÃ¡o SNS</strong> khi <strong>uptime giáº£m xuá»‘ng dÆ°á»›i 99%</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Giáº£i phÃ¡p pháº£i <strong>pháº£n Ã¡nh chÃ­nh xÃ¡c tráº£i nghiá»‡m thá»±c táº¿</strong> cá»§a ngÆ°á»i dÃ¹ng khi truy cáº­p website</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âœ… <strong><u>ÄÃ¡p Ã¡n Ä‘Ãºng:</u></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Create an Amazon CloudWatch Synthetics heartbeat monitoring canary. Associate the canary with the website's URL for end users. Create a CloudWatch alarm for the canary. Configure the alarm to publish an SNS notification if the value of the SuccessPercent metric is less than 99%.</strong></p>\n\n<p>ÄÃ¢y lÃ  giáº£i phÃ¡p Ä‘Ãºng vÃ¬ sá»­ dá»¥ng <strong>CloudWatch Synthetics canary</strong> dáº¡ng <strong>heartbeat monitoring</strong> - cÃ´ng cá»¥ Ä‘Æ°á»£c thiáº¿t káº¿ Ä‘á»ƒ mÃ´ phá»ng hÃ nh vi ngÆ°á»i dÃ¹ng thá»±c táº¿ truy cáº­p website.</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>Canary heartbeat</strong> sáº½ tá»± Ä‘á»™ng truy cáº­p URL cá»§a website theo lá»‹ch Ä‘á»‹nh ká»³ (giá»‘ng ngÆ°á»i dÃ¹ng tháº­t), kiá»ƒm tra xem website cÃ³ pháº£n há»“i thÃ nh cÃ´ng hay khÃ´ng</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Chá»‰ sá»‘ <strong>SuccessPercent</strong> Ä‘o chÃ­nh xÃ¡c tá»· lá»‡ thÃ nh cÃ´ng cá»§a cÃ¡c láº§n truy cáº­p - khi giÃ¡ trá»‹ nÃ y dÆ°á»›i 99% nghÄ©a lÃ  uptime giáº£m xuá»‘ng dÆ°á»›i ngÆ°á»¡ng yÃªu cáº§u</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>CloudWatch Alarm</strong> sáº½ kÃ­ch hoáº¡t SNS notification ngay khi phÃ¡t hiá»‡n SuccessPercent < 99%, Ä‘Ã¡p á»©ng Ä‘áº§y Ä‘á»§ yÃªu cáº§u giÃ¡m sÃ¡t vÃ  cáº£nh bÃ¡o</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Canary cháº¡y tá»« nhiá»u <strong>vá»‹ trÃ­ Ä‘á»‹a lÃ½ khÃ¡c nhau</strong>, mÃ´ phá»ng chÃ­nh xÃ¡c tráº£i nghiá»‡m cá»§a ngÆ°á»i dÃ¹ng cuá»‘i (end user experience) - khÃ´ng chá»‰ kiá»ƒm tra tá»« server-side</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <u><strong>CÃ¡c Ä‘Ã¡p Ã¡n sai:</strong></u></p>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create an Amazon CloudWatch alarm that is based on the website's logs that are published to a CloudWatch Logs log group. Configure the alarm to publish an SNS notification if the number of HTTP 4xx errors and 5xx errors exceeds a specified threshold.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>PhÆ°Æ¡ng phÃ¡p nÃ y chá»‰ giÃ¡m sÃ¡t <strong>lá»—i HTTP tá»« phÃ­a server</strong>, khÃ´ng pháº£n Ã¡nh chÃ­nh xÃ¡c <strong>tráº£i nghiá»‡m ngÆ°á»i dÃ¹ng cuá»‘i</strong> (vÃ­ dá»¥: website cÃ³ thá»ƒ bá»‹ cháº­m hoáº·c khÃ´ng truy cáº­p Ä‘Æ°á»£c tá»« má»™t sá»‘ khu vá»±c Ä‘á»‹a lÃ½ nhÆ°ng khÃ´ng táº¡o ra lá»—i 4xx/5xx)</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>KhÃ´ng tÃ­nh toÃ¡n Ä‘Æ°á»£c <strong>uptime dÆ°á»›i 99%</strong> má»™t cÃ¡ch chÃ­nh xÃ¡c - chá»‰ Ä‘áº¿m sá»‘ lÆ°á»£ng lá»—i vÆ°á»£t ngÆ°á»¡ng, khÃ´ng pháº£i tá»· lá»‡ pháº§n trÄƒm thÃ nh cÃ´ng</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create an Amazon CloudWatch alarm that is based on the website's published metrics in CloudWatch. Configure the alarm to publish an SNS notification that is based on anomaly detection.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>Anomaly detection</strong> (phÃ¡t hiá»‡n báº¥t thÆ°á»ng) chá»‰ cáº£nh bÃ¡o khi cÃ³ sá»± thay Ä‘á»•i báº¥t thÆ°á»ng so vá»›i pattern trÆ°á»›c Ä‘Ã³, khÃ´ng giÃ¡m sÃ¡t ngÆ°á»¡ng uptime cá»‘ Ä‘á»‹nh 99%</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>KhÃ´ng Ä‘o lÆ°á»ng <strong>tráº£i nghiá»‡m ngÆ°á»i dÃ¹ng cuá»‘i</strong> - chá»‰ dá»±a vÃ o metrics tá»« phÃ­a server, khÃ´ng mÃ´ phá»ng hÃ nh vi truy cáº­p thá»±c táº¿</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create an Amazon CloudWatch Synthetics broken link checker monitoring canary. Associate the canary with the website's URL for end users. Create a CloudWatch alarm for the canary. Configure the alarm to publish an SNS notification if the value of the SuccessPercent metric is less than 99%.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>Broken link checker canary</strong> Ä‘Æ°á»£c thiáº¿t káº¿ Ä‘á»ƒ <strong>kiá»ƒm tra cÃ¡c liÃªn káº¿t bá»‹ há»ng</strong> (broken links) trÃªn website, khÃ´ng pháº£i Ä‘á»ƒ Ä‘o uptime/availability</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Má»¥c Ä‘Ã­ch chÃ­nh cá»§a loáº¡i canary nÃ y lÃ  tÃ¬m cÃ¡c link ná»™i bá»™ khÃ´ng hoáº¡t Ä‘á»™ng, khÃ´ng phÃ¹ há»£p vá»›i yÃªu cáº§u giÃ¡m sÃ¡t tÃ­nh kháº£ dá»¥ng tá»•ng thá»ƒ cá»§a website</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ”‘<strong><u>Tips and tricks:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>User experience</strong>\" + \"<strong>website availability</strong>\" â†’ <strong>CloudWatch Synthetics Canary</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Uptime percentage</strong>\" + \"<strong>monitoring</strong>\" â†’ <strong>Heartbeat canary vá»›i SuccessPercent metric</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Broken links</strong>\" â†’ <strong>Broken link checker canary</strong> (khÃ¡c vá»›i heartbeat monitoring)</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ“– <strong><u>Reference:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudWatch/latest/monitoring/CloudWatch_Synthetics_Canaries.html\">CloudWatch Synthetics Canaries</a></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudWatch/latest/monitoring/CloudWatch_Synthetics_Canaries_Blueprints.html\">Canary Blueprints (Heartbeat vs Broken Link Checker)</a></p>\n    </li>\n</ul>",
