            "questionText": "<p>A media company hosts a public news and video portal on AWS. The portal uses an Amazon DynamoDB table with provisioned capacity to maintain an index of video files that are stored in an Amazon S3 bucket. During a recent event, millions of visitors came to the portal for news. This increase in traffic caused read requests to be throttled in the DynamoDB table. Videos could not be displayed in the portal.<br><br>The company's operations team manually increased the provisioned capacity on a temporary basis to meet the demand. The company wants the operations team to receive an alert before the table is throttled in the future. The company has created an Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) topic and has subscribed the operations team's email address to the SNS topic.<br><br>What should the company do next to meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>ğŸ“ <strong><u>TÃ³m táº¯t Ä‘á»:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>CÃ´ng ty truyá»n thÃ´ng cÃ³ cá»•ng tin tá»©c, sá»­ dá»¥ng <strong>DynamoDB vá»›i provisioned capacity</strong> Ä‘á»ƒ lÆ°u danh má»¥c video</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Khi lÆ°á»£ng truy cáº­p tÄƒng Ä‘á»™t biáº¿n â†’ bá»‹ <strong>throttled</strong> (DynamoDB tá»« chá»‘i yÃªu cáº§u Ä‘á»c vÃ¬ vÆ°á»£t quÃ¡ capacity)</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>YÃªu cáº§u: <strong>cáº£nh bÃ¡o trÆ°á»›c</strong> khi sáº¯p bá»‹ throttled (khÃ´ng pháº£i sau khi Ä‘Ã£ throttled) â†’ team váº­n hÃ nh ká»‹p xá»­ lÃ½</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>ÄÃ£ cÃ³ SNS topic sáºµn Ä‘á»ƒ gá»­i email thÃ´ng bÃ¡o</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âœ… <strong><u>ÄÃ¡p Ã¡n Ä‘Ãºng:</u></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Create an Amazon CloudWatch alarm that uses the ConsumedReadCapacityUnits metric. Set the alarm threshold to a value that is close to the DynamoDB table's provisioned capacity. Configure the alarm to publish notifications to the SNS topic.</strong></p>\n\n<p>Giáº£i phÃ¡p nÃ y Ä‘Ãºng vÃ¬ thá»a mÃ£n yÃªu cáº§u <strong>cáº£nh bÃ¡o trÆ°á»›c</strong> khi sáº¯p bá»‹ throttled:</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>ConsumedReadCapacityUnits</strong> lÃ  chá»‰ sá»‘ Ä‘o lÆ°á»£ng capacity Ä‘Ã£ sá»­ dá»¥ng cá»§a DynamoDB â†’ khi chá»‰ sá»‘ nÃ y tiáº¿n gáº§n Ä‘áº¿n giá»›i háº¡n provisioned capacity, nghÄ©a lÃ  sáº¯p bá»‹ throttled</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Äáº·t ngÆ°á»¡ng cáº£nh bÃ¡o (threshold) á»Ÿ má»©c <strong>gáº§n vá»›i provisioned capacity</strong> (vÃ­ dá»¥: 80-90%) â†’ CloudWatch alarm sáº½ kÃ­ch hoáº¡t trÆ°á»›c khi throttling xáº£y ra</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>CloudWatch alarm tá»± Ä‘á»™ng gá»­i thÃ´ng bÃ¡o Ä‘áº¿n SNS topic â†’ team nháº­n email vÃ  ká»‹p thá»i tÄƒng capacity</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>CÃ¡ch tiáº¿p cáº­n nÃ y mang tÃ­nh <strong>proactive</strong> (phÃ²ng ngá»«a) thay vÃ¬ reactive (pháº£n á»©ng sau sá»± cá»‘)</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <u><strong>CÃ¡c Ä‘Ã¡p Ã¡n sai:</strong></u></p>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Turn on auto scaling on the DynamoDB table. Configure an Amazon EventBridge rule to publish notifications to the SNS topic during scaling events.</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>Auto scaling tá»± Ä‘á»™ng tÄƒng capacity khi cáº§n â†’ giáº£i quyáº¿t váº¥n Ä‘á» throttling nhÆ°ng <strong>khÃ´ng gá»­i cáº£nh bÃ¡o trÆ°á»›c</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>EventBridge chá»‰ thÃ´ng bÃ¡o khi scaling Ä‘Ã£ xáº£y ra (sau khi throttling báº¯t Ä‘áº§u) â†’ khÃ´ng Ä‘Ã¡p á»©ng yÃªu cáº§u cáº£nh bÃ¡o trÆ°á»›c</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Turn on Amazon CloudWatch Logs for the DynamoDB table. Create an Amazon CloudWatch metric filter to pattern match the THROTTLING_EXCEPTION status code from DynamoDB. Create a CloudWatch alarm for the metric. Select the SNS topic for notifications.</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>Báº¯t lá»—i THROTTLING_EXCEPTION cÃ³ nghÄ©a lÃ  throttling <strong>Ä‘Ã£ xáº£y ra rá»“i</strong> â†’ cáº£nh bÃ¡o muá»™n, khÃ´ng Ä‘Ã¡p á»©ng yÃªu cáº§u cáº£nh bÃ¡o trÆ°á»›c</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>DynamoDB khÃ´ng cÃ³ tÃ­nh nÄƒng CloudWatch Logs máº·c Ä‘á»‹nh cho viá»‡c theo dÃµi throttling nhÆ° cÃ¡ch nÃ y mÃ´ táº£</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Configure the application to store logs in Amazon CloudWatch Logs. Create an Amazon CloudWatch metric filter to pattern match the THROTTLING_EXCEPTION status code from DynamoDB. Create a CloudWatch alarm for the metric. Select the SNS topic for notifications.</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>TÆ°Æ¡ng tá»± Ä‘Ã¡p Ã¡n trÃªn, chá»‰ cáº£nh bÃ¡o sau khi throttling Ä‘Ã£ xáº£y ra, khÃ´ng pháº£i trÆ°á»›c</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Phá»¥ thuá»™c vÃ o application logs â†’ thÃªm Ä‘á»™ phá»©c táº¡p vÃ  khÃ´ng cáº§n thiáº¿t khi CloudWatch cÃ³ sáºµn metric ConsumedReadCapacityUnits</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ”‘<strong><u>Tips and tricks:</u></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Cáº£nh bÃ¡o trÆ°á»›c (alert before)</strong>\" â†’ DÃ¹ng <strong>ConsumedReadCapacityUnits metric + CloudWatch Alarm</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>THROTTLING_EXCEPTION</strong>\" â†’ Cáº£nh bÃ¡o muá»™n (sau khi throttled), khÃ´ng phÃ¹ há»£p cho yÃªu cáº§u proactive</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Auto Scaling</strong>\" â†’ Tá»± Ä‘á»™ng xá»­ lÃ½ throttling nhÆ°ng khÃ´ng gá»­i cáº£nh bÃ¡o trÆ°á»›c</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ“– <strong><u>Reference:</u></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/amazondynamodb/latest/developerguide/metrics-dimensions.html\">DynamoDB CloudWatch Metrics</a></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudWatch/latest/monitoring/AlarmThatSendsEmail.html\">CloudWatch Alarms with SNS</a></p>\n    </li>\n</ul>",
