            "questionText": "<p>A company has deployed an application on AWS. The application runs on a fleet of Linux Amazon EC2 instances that are in an Auto Scaling group. The Auto Scaling group is configured to use launch templates. The launch templates launch Amazon Elastic Block Store (Amazon EBS) backed EC2 instances that use General Purpose SSD (gp3) EBS volumes for primary storage.<br><br>A SysOps administrator needs to implement a solution to ensure that all the EC2 instances can share the same underlying files. The solution also must ensure that the data is consistent.<br><br>Which solution will meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>ğŸ“ <strong><u>TÃ³m táº¯t Ä‘á»:</u></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>CÃ´ng ty cÃ³ á»©ng dá»¥ng cháº¡y trÃªn nhÃ³m cÃ¡c <strong>EC2 instances trong Auto Scaling group</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Hiá»‡n táº¡i má»—i EC2 Ä‘ang dÃ¹ng <strong>EBS volume riÃªng biá»‡t (gp3)</strong> lÃ m storage chÃ­nh</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>YÃªu cáº§u: Táº¥t cáº£ cÃ¡c EC2 instances cáº§n <strong>chia sáº» cÃ¹ng file</strong> vÃ  Ä‘áº£m báº£o <strong>dá»¯ liá»‡u nháº¥t quÃ¡n (consistent)</strong></p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âœ… <strong><u>ÄÃ¡p Ã¡n Ä‘Ãºng:</u></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Create an Amazon Elastic File System (Amazon EFS) file system. Create a new launch template version that includes user data that mounts the EFS file system. Update the Auto Scaling group to use the new launch template version to cycle in newer EC2 instances and to terminate the older EC2 instances.</strong></p>\n\n<p>CÃ¢u nÃ y Ä‘Ãºng vÃ¬ <strong>EFS lÃ  dá»‹ch vá»¥ lÆ°u trá»¯ file Ä‘Æ°á»£c thiáº¿t káº¿ Ä‘áº·c biá»‡t Ä‘á»ƒ nhiá»u EC2 cÃ¹ng truy cáº­p Ä‘á»“ng thá»i</strong>. EFS hoáº¡t Ä‘á»™ng nhÆ° má»™t á»• Ä‘Ä©a máº¡ng mÃ  táº¥t cáº£ cÃ¡c mÃ¡y chá»§ Ä‘á»u cÃ³ thá»ƒ káº¿t ná»‘i vÃ o vÃ  Ä‘á»c/ghi file chung.</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>EFS tá»± Ä‘á»™ng Ä‘áº£m báº£o tÃ­nh nháº¥t quÃ¡n dá»¯ liá»‡u</strong> - khi má»™t instance ghi file, cÃ¡c instance khÃ¡c sáº½ tháº¥y ngay láº­p tá»©c phiÃªn báº£n má»›i nháº¥t</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>DÃ¹ng user data trong launch template</strong> Ä‘á»ƒ tá»± Ä‘á»™ng mount (gáº¯n káº¿t) EFS vÃ o EC2 khi instance khá»Ÿi Ä‘á»™ng - Ä‘áº£m báº£o má»i instance má»›i Ä‘á»u tá»± Ä‘á»™ng cÃ³ quyá»n truy cáº­p file chung</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>Scale tá»± Ä‘á»™ng</strong> - khi Auto Scaling thÃªm/bá»›t instance, cÃ¡c instance má»›i tá»± Ä‘á»™ng káº¿t ná»‘i vÃ o cÃ¹ng EFS Ä‘Ã³ mÃ  khÃ´ng cáº§n cáº¥u hÃ¬nh thÃªm</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <u><strong>CÃ¡c Ä‘Ã¡p Ã¡n sai:</strong></u></p>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Enable Multi-Attach on the EBS volumes. Create a new launch template version that includes user data that mounts the EBS volume. Update the Auto Scaling group to use the new template version to cycle in newer EC2 instances and to terminate the older EC2 instances.</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>TÃ­nh nÄƒng Multi-Attach cá»§a EBS chá»‰ há»— trá»£ <strong>tá»‘i Ä‘a 16 instances cÃ¹ng lÃºc</strong> vÃ  chá»‰ hoáº¡t Ä‘á»™ng trong <strong>cÃ¹ng má»™t Availability Zone</strong> - khÃ´ng phÃ¹ há»£p cho Auto Scaling cÃ³ thá»ƒ má»Ÿ rá»™ng nhiá»u hÆ¡n hoáº·c cháº¡y trÃªn nhiá»u AZ</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Multi-Attach <strong>khÃ´ng tá»± Ä‘á»™ng Ä‘áº£m báº£o tÃ­nh nháº¥t quÃ¡n</strong> - báº¡n pháº£i tá»± quáº£n lÃ½ file system clustering (nhÆ° GFS2 hoáº·c OCFS2) ráº¥t phá»©c táº¡p</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create a cron job that synchronizes the data between the EBS volumes for all the EC2 instances in the Auto Scaling group. Create a lifecycle hook during instance launch to configure the cron job on all the EC2 instances. Rotate out the older EC2 instances.</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>DÃ¹ng cron job Ä‘á»ƒ Ä‘á»“ng bá»™ dá»¯ liá»‡u <strong>khÃ´ng Ä‘áº£m báº£o tÃ­nh nháº¥t quÃ¡n theo thá»i gian thá»±c</strong> - sáº½ cÃ³ Ä‘á»™ trá»… giá»¯a cÃ¡c láº§n cháº¡y Ä‘á»“ng bá»™, cÃ¡c instance cÃ³ thá»ƒ tháº¥y dá»¯ liá»‡u cÅ©</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Giáº£i phÃ¡p nÃ y <strong>phá»©c táº¡p vÃ  dá»… lá»—i</strong> - pháº£i tá»± viáº¿t script Ä‘á»“ng bá»™, xá»­ lÃ½ xung Ä‘á»™t file, vÃ  quáº£n lÃ½ bandwidth cho viá»‡c copy dá»¯ liá»‡u liÃªn tá»¥c</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create a new launch template version that creates an Amazon Elastic File System (Amazon EFS) file system. Update the Auto Scaling group to use the new template version to cycle in newer EC2 instances and to terminate the older EC2 instances.</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>Launch template khÃ´ng thá»ƒ táº¡o EFS file system</strong> - launch template chá»‰ dÃ¹ng Ä‘á»ƒ cáº¥u hÃ¬nh EC2 instance (CPU, memory, storage, network)</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>EFS pháº£i Ä‘Æ°á»£c táº¡o riÃªng trÆ°á»›c (qua console, CLI, hoáº·c CloudFormation), sau Ä‘Ã³ má»›i mount vÃ o EC2 thÃ´ng qua user data</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ”‘<strong><u>Tips and tricks:</u></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Shared files + multiple EC2</strong>\" â†’ <strong>Amazon EFS</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Auto Scaling + consistent data</strong>\" â†’ <strong>EFS vá»›i user data mount</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>EBS Multi-Attach</strong>\" â†’ <strong>Chá»‰ dÃ¹ng cho use case Ä‘áº·c biá»‡t (HA cluster), khÃ´ng pháº£i shared storage thÃ´ng thÆ°á»ng</strong></p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ“– <strong><u>Reference:</u></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/whatisefs.html\">Amazon EFS - What is Amazon EFS</a></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/mounting-fs.html\">Mounting EFS file systems</a></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ebs-volumes-multi.html\">EBS Multi-Attach limitations</a></p>\n    </li>\n</ul>",
