            "questionText": "<p>A company is running workloads on premises and on AWS. A SysOps administrator needs to automate tasks across all servers on premises by using AWS services. The SysOps administrator must not install long-term credentials on the on-premises servers.<br><br>What should the SysOps administrator do to meet these requirements?</p>",
            "explanation": "<p>ğŸ“ <strong><u>TÃ³m táº¯t Ä‘á»:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>CÃ´ng ty Ä‘ang cháº¡y workloads <strong>vá»«a trÃªn AWS vá»«a trÃªn on-premises</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>SysOps Admin cáº§n <strong>tá»± Ä‘á»™ng hÃ³a cÃ¡c tÃ¡c vá»¥ trÃªn táº¥t cáº£ mÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises</strong> báº±ng cÃ¡c dá»‹ch vá»¥ AWS</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>YÃªu cáº§u quan trá»ng: <strong>KHÃ”NG Ä‘Æ°á»£c cÃ i Ä‘áº·t long-term credentials</strong> (khÃ´ng lÆ°u access key lÃ¢u dÃ i) trÃªn cÃ¡c mÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âœ… <strong><u>ÄÃ¡p Ã¡n Ä‘Ãºng:</u></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Create a managed-instance activation in AWS Systems Manager. Install the Systems Manager Agent (SSM Agent) on the on-premises servers. Register the servers with the activation code and ID from the instance activation.</strong></p>\n\n<p>ÄÃ¢y chÃ­nh xÃ¡c lÃ  cÃ¡ch AWS thiáº¿t káº¿ Ä‘á»ƒ quáº£n lÃ½ mÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises má»™t cÃ¡ch báº£o máº­t mÃ  khÃ´ng cáº§n lÆ°u trá»¯ access key lÃ¢u dÃ i trÃªn mÃ¡y chá»§.</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><strong>Managed-instance activation</strong> táº¡o ra má»™t cáº·p <strong>Activation Code vÃ  Activation ID</strong> (giá»‘ng nhÆ° máº­t kháº©u vÃ  tÃªn Ä‘Äƒng nháº­p táº¡m thá»i) Ä‘á»ƒ Ä‘Äƒng kÃ½ mÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises vá»›i Systems Manager</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Khi cÃ i <strong>SSM Agent</strong> vÃ  Ä‘Äƒng kÃ½ báº±ng activation code/ID, mÃ¡y chá»§ sáº½ tá»± Ä‘á»™ng nháº­n quyá»n tá»« <strong>IAM role</strong> Ä‘Æ°á»£c gáº¯n vá»›i activation - khÃ´ng cáº§n lÆ°u access key nÃ o trÃªn mÃ¡y chá»§</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>Sau khi Ä‘Äƒng kÃ½ thÃ nh cÃ´ng, SSM Agent sáº½ tá»± Ä‘á»™ng duy trÃ¬ káº¿t ná»‘i vá»›i Systems Manager vÃ  sá»­ dá»¥ng temporary credentials do IAM role cung cáº¥p (credentials nÃ y tá»± Ä‘á»™ng lÃ m má»›i)</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>ÄÃ¡p á»©ng Ä‘áº§y Ä‘á»§ yÃªu cáº§u: <strong>tá»± Ä‘á»™ng hÃ³a tÃ¡c vá»¥</strong> qua Systems Manager (Run Command, State Manager...) vÃ  <strong>khÃ´ng cÃ i long-term credentials</strong> trÃªn mÃ¡y chá»§</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <u><strong>CÃ¡c Ä‘Ã¡p Ã¡n sai:</strong></u></p>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create an IAM role and instance profile that include AWS Systems Manager permissions. Attach the role to the on-premises servers.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>Instance profile chá»‰ hoáº¡t Ä‘á»™ng vá»›i EC2 instances, khÃ´ng thá»ƒ attach trá»±c tiáº¿p vÃ o mÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>MÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises khÃ´ng cÃ³ metadata service nhÆ° EC2 Ä‘á»ƒ láº¥y temporary credentials tá»« instance profile</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create an AWS managed IAM policy that includes the appropriate AWS Systems Manager permissions. Download the IAM policy to the on-premises servers.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>IAM policy chá»‰ lÃ  táº­p quy táº¯c Ä‘á»‹nh nghÄ©a quyá»n háº¡n, khÃ´ng pháº£i lÃ  credentials - khÃ´ng thá»ƒ \"download\" vÃ  sá»­ dá»¥ng trá»±c tiáº¿p Ä‘á»ƒ xÃ¡c thá»±c vá»›i AWS</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>KhÃ´ng giáº£i quyáº¿t Ä‘Æ°á»£c váº¥n Ä‘á» lÃ m sao mÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises cÃ³ thá»ƒ xÃ¡c thá»±c vá»›i AWS mÃ  khÃ´ng cáº§n long-term credentials</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>âŒ <strong>Create an IAM user and an access key. Log on to the on-premises servers and install the AWS CLI. Configure the access key in the AWS credentials file after the AWS CLI is successfully installed.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>Access key lÃ  <strong>long-term credentials</strong> - vi pháº¡m trá»±c tiáº¿p yÃªu cáº§u Ä‘á» bÃ i vá» viá»‡c khÃ´ng Ä‘Æ°á»£c cÃ i long-term credentials</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>LÆ°u access key trong credentials file lÃ  thá»±c hÃ nh khÃ´ng an toÃ n, dá»… bá»‹ lá»™ vÃ  khÃ³ quáº£n lÃ½/rotate</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ”‘<strong><u>Tips and tricks:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>On-premises + khÃ´ng dÃ¹ng long-term credentials</strong>\" â†’ <strong>Systems Manager Hybrid Activation</strong></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Activation Code vÃ  Activation ID</strong>\" â†’ CÃ¡ch Ä‘Äƒng kÃ½ mÃ¡y chá»§ on-premises vá»›i Systems Manager</p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p>\"<strong>Instance profile</strong>\" â†’ Chá»‰ dÃ nh cho EC2, khÃ´ng dÃ¹ng cho on-premises</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p></p><p>ğŸ“– <strong><u>Reference:</u></strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/systems-manager/latest/userguide/hybrid-activation-managed-nodes.html\">Create a hybrid activation - AWS Systems Manager</a></p>\n    </li>\n    <li>\n        <p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/systems-manager/latest/userguide/activations.html\">AWS Systems Manager Hybrid Activations</a></p>\n    </li>\n</ul>",
